      "message": "It\u0027s not ENTIRELY misleading! fields.fLength does set a reasonable upper bound; for a two-element swizzle, the maximum size of `shuffleComponents` will never exceed 2 (it can\u0027t contain two constants). However, I agree that 3 is also a sane upper bound with a better outcome in the common case, so I will change it. (min(fields.fLength, 3) is an even tighter bound but not worth the complexity.)",
